        {
            "name": "Shadow Giant",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [],
            "text": "Shadow giants are natives of the Plane of Shadow, where they have dwelled in perpetual twilight for millennia. Their cultures vary greatly depending on whether the giants reside in their land of origin or have relocated to the Material Plane. On the Plane of Shadow, they live in familial groups and uphold a nomadic way of life as they roam across vast ancestral lands between forests of shadow and misty chasms. These hunter-gatherers pass their lore down through oral histories, conduct pilgrimages to unholy ziggurats of black stone, and bathe in the blood of their long-standing foes, including rival shadow giant tribes and velstracs intent on enslaving their kind. On the Material Plane, conversely, they are typically secretive and isolationist, keeping apart from other peoples.<br/><br/> Standing 15 feet tall, with gray skin and hair only a shade lighter, shadow giants are fearsome foes with a well-earned reputation as fierce warmongers and ruthless combatants. They rarely interact with outsiders, though they may treat with proven warriors who show the giants the respect and deference they feel they deserve. Only a small subset of shadow giants worship Zon-Kuthon, and most of these Kuthites are so firmly entrenched in the culture of Nidal that their Shadow Plane\u2013dwelling brethren would hardly recognize them. Most shadow giants instead practice an ancient religion that, while unique to their people, many confuse with the faith of Zon-Kuthon, as it has its own bloody themes of sacrifice and self-mutilation.<br/><br/><br/><b><u><a aonid=\"5\" game-obj=\"Skills\" general=\"true\">Recall Knowledge - Humanoid</a></u> (<u><a aonid=\"14\" game-obj=\"Skills\">Society</a></u>)</b>: DC 31",
            "source": {
                "name": "Pathfinder #147: Tomorrow Must Burn",
                "link": {
                    "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zrs?Pathfinder-Adventure-Path-147-Tomorrow-Must-Burn"
                },
                "page": 79
            }
        },
        {
            "name": "Giant",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "Giant Bags",
                    "type": "sidebar",
                    "sections": [],
                    "text": "Giants often keep an eclectic collection of treasures in their knapsacks or bags. Among these can be found a staggeringly wide range of unexpected and odd treasures and valuables.",
                    "source": {
                        "name": "Bestiary",
                        "link": {
                            "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01y0m?Pathfinder-Bestiary"
                        },
                        "page": 170
                    },
                    "subtype": "treasure_and_rewards",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Treasure and Rewards",
                    "image": "Sidebar_5_TreasureAndRewards.png"
                },
                {
                    "name": "Giant Locations",
                    "type": "sidebar",
                    "sections": [],
                    "text": "As oversized as they are, giants tend to dwell in remote regions of the world, where they have the luxury of claiming larger territories of their own.",
                    "source": {
                        "name": "Bestiary",
                        "link": {
                            "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01y0m?Pathfinder-Bestiary"
                        },
                        "page": 170
                    },
                    "subtype": "locations",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Locations",
                    "image": "Sidebar_3_Locations.png"
                },
                {
                    "name": "Giant Pets",
                    "type": "sidebar",
                    "sections": [],
                    "text": "As with many people, giants enjoy keeping pets. Yet for giants, what constitutes a pet is often categorized as beast to others. Large animals like bears and lions, and megafauna like woolly mammoths and dinosaurs are popular, as are more magical creatures like hell hounds, manticores, griffons, and the like.",
                    "source": {
                        "name": "Bestiary",
                        "link": {
                            "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01y0m?Pathfinder-Bestiary"
                        },
                        "page": 170
                    },
                    "subtype": "related_creatures",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Related Creatures",
                    "image": "Sidebar_4_RelatedCreatures.png"
                },
                {
                    "name": "Other Giants",
                    "type": "sidebar",
                    "sections": [],
                    "text": "Beyond the giants detailed here, many others dwell in remote regions of the world. Marsh giants are cultists who worship strange sea deities, shadow giants have ties to the Shadow Plane, and mountain giants are horrific butchers even other giants fear.",
                    "source": {
                        "name": "Bestiary",
                        "link": {
                            "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01y0m?Pathfinder-Bestiary"
                        },
                        "page": 170
                    },
                    "subtype": "related_creatures",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Related Creatures",
                    "image": "Sidebar_4_RelatedCreatures.png"
                },
                {
                    "name": "Oversized Themes",
                    "type": "sidebar",
                    "sections": [],
                    "text": "Giants are larger-than-life foes. While many giants have themes that tie them to elemental or magical forces, the primary theme giants share is that they embody a classic cultural trope as their basis. Fire giants, for example, can be seen as oversized smiths, while hill giants should evoke the flavor of an oversized bully.",
                    "source": {
                        "name": "Bestiary",
                        "link": {
                            "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01y0m?Pathfinder-Bestiary"
                        },
                        "page": 170
                    },
                    "subtype": "advice_and_rules",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Advice and Rules",
                    "image": "Sidebar_1_AdviceAndRules.png"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Giants are massive humanoid creatures who live in remote regions throughout the world. They are divided into a number of subtypes.",
            "source": {
                "name": "Bestiary",
                "link": {
                    "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01y0m?Pathfinder-Bestiary"
                },
                "page": 170
            }
        }
